<Author>mkurozen
<Content>Very Satisfied with the Stay We were a group of 3 that booked 2 rooms at the hotel for a 3 night stay. Overall, we were very satisfied with our stay. The location is acceptable, we felt safe and the hotel was not too far from the main attractions. For avid walkers such as me and my wife, walking everywhere was quite pleasant--we walked to all of the main attractons which also gave us the opportunity to explore the local residential areas. The train station for both TMB and Renfe (for to/from Airport) are within less than 5 minutes walk (Station El Clot). It takes approximately 1 hour to reach the airport at a cost of 2.60 Euros. As far as the rooms, the staff and breakfast, all was above average. Upon check-in, the receptionist was very nice and pleasant, spoke English (slightly worrisome because none in our party speaks Spanish) and even gave us vouchers for a free Cava at the bar. The room was large enough by European standards, easy to get to both by elevator and stairs (which were actually well-lit as it faced the front and had glass panes). Most important of all, the room was clean. The breakfast was just fine with enough choices. The price was included in our stay which made it all the better. The cheese/marmalade sandwiches, tuna sandwiches (yes for breakfast!) and sardine sandwiches were excellent. There was also a hot griddle for eggs which we did not try. We never felt unsafe in the area of the hotel as walked back each night typically after 11:30 PM.  Overall, I would rate the stay above average for the price we paid and would definitely stay here again. 
