<Author>gcjones
<Content>What A Pleasant Surprise! At the end of our 12-day jaunt through London, France and Barcelona, our group stayed two nights at the Catalonia Aragon. What a wonderful surprise. It's about 6-8 blocks east of the marvelous Sagrada Familia cathedral, near the Clot metro stop. The neighborhood is working-class, but we didn't feel unsafe walking to the cathedral in the evening. The rooms were spacious (by European standards), and it was evident that they had been recently redone. The breakfast/restaurant was excellent -- we had a great buffet supper, and breakfast the next morning had cook-to-order omelettes available, along with steamed tomatoes, cheeses, meats, cereals, etc! The staff was most helpful, and spoke very passable English, offering to briefly stow our luggage while we ate breakfast before heading to the Estancia Franca train station to catch our train to Lyon (we had stayed behind, the rest of the group had left at 3 am to catch their flight). The also were most helpful in getting a taxi for us to the train station. I'd definitely stay there again. 
