<Author>scm1133
<Content>Pleasantly Surprised! We stayed at the Catalona Aragon for 3 nights and were pleasantly surprised with the experience at the hotel. It was a lovely stay. Having read numerous reviews, we were a bit reluctant, but it worked out. Customer Service: It was impeccable - the front desk staff were as helpful as possible, some more than others, but always to the best of their ability. They checked tickets for concerts, bullfights, and looked into dinner reservations.Location: Some reviews noted that the hotel was far away - it depends on what you are looking to do and where you are planning to go - we found the hotel very accessible. It is a 2 minute walk to Clot metro station, which is on the L2 and very well connected without needing multiple transfers. That said, given the nice weather, we took a few nice walks to La Sagrada Familia and even all the way to Las Ramblas and did not find it too much trouble - it was a great location. We were able to see a few less touristy spots and eat a few more authentic meals than if we'd stayed directly in the city center. We stayed for 4 full days and did not use up our T-10 metro cards!Despite the fact that everyone raved about the breakfast - we did not eat it, instead, we opted for amazing .65 croissants at the bakery just 1 block past the hotel (away from the metro) - amazing, fresh, and much better than the 12 euro option at the hotel! Also, 'Isabels' is a local convenient store - .77 for a 1.5L bottle of water - if you are walking into town, better to buy it there, because at La Sagrada Familiar the same bottle was 2.50 euros.Booking: We booked on laterooms.com where the rate was substantially lower than the website and expedia. Then, I emailed the reservation staff at the Aragon, who emailed back promptly and worked with me to ensure that the room had 2 beds pushed together so that my boyfriend and I did not have to sleep across the room - very very helpful. Then, reservations surprised me by sending an envelope of 'Barcelona' information - tours, exhibits, etc to my apartment, which arrived before we left so that we could start to plan out our trip.We hope this helps! We would definitely return to the hotel - clean, modern, and very refreshing! 
