<Content>Another great stay in Barcelona We were transferred from the adjacent Hotel Albeniz, and we probably received better value at this hotel. The bedroom smelt a little smoky, and was fairly small, but it was clean and comfortable, with a modern bathroom, with both bath and shower. There was plenty of choice at the breakfast buffet, with omelettes available, cooked to order, as well as the usual selection of food. We did receive an unnecessarily surly reception when we arrived before 7.30.a.m. on Saturday; breakfast is served half-an-hour later at weekends.The hotel is a very short walk from the Clot Metro station, and we saved a lot of time and money by purchasing five-day travel tickets (which permit access to bus and metro.)This was our third visit to Barcelona, and it gets better each time, with so much to see, and such beautiful colours. This time we included a tour of the fantastic Palau Musica de Catalunya, and also participated in an excusion to Montserrat, Sitges and a winery, as well as visiting the normal Gaudi haunts. Hotel Aragon was fine for our purpose. Our only complaint about the holiday was having to fly home at the end !!!! 
