<Content>got back today Just returned from three nights at the Catalonia Aragon. Booked the trip as a present for my husband but was a bit worried after reading the reviews on the site. There was no need to I'm glad to say.We arrived about 11pm, the girl on reception was perfectly pleasant and polite the whole time- she even smiled more than once- contrary to the info on other reviews. The hotel is built around a corner and some of the rooms can be difficult to find. We couldn't find ours but just went back to reception to ask and someone came with us.The public areas of the hotel have seen a bit better days, but they are trying to tidy them up a bit. There was notice in reception to this effect and one of the walls was painted while we were there. Some of the public areas are also being used as store rooms for mattresses and towels. I didn't mention it to any of the staff so don't know whether this is usual or not.The rooms themselves are fine, ours wasn't huge but there was plenty of room for two of us, everything was clean and tidy, the bed was comfy, loads of hot water, the heating control worked and the maid gave us clean towels and new toiletries every day. Breakfast was 7.30 to 10.30 every day and 7.30 til 11 am on Sunday. There was everything you could want to eat and more both hot  cold. The staff in the restaurant smiled too!Not much in the way of bars and restaurants right by the hotel but you pass plenty if you walk 2 streets back from the hotel toward Segrada Familia. For the price I paid I believe I got good value and would be happy to stay here again. The only drawback was the distance from the ramblas, place catalunya etc. We tended to have breakfast and leave for the day and just came back after our evening meal about 11pm. Had we been staying a bit more central we may have gone back to the hotel late afternoon for a bit of a rest. But instead we had to find a bar with some tasty tapas and a smooth red wine.... such hardship! 
